    Architecture

[Camera] → (HTTP/Private/FTP) → [Alarm Server] → (zabbix_sender) → [Zabbix Server]
              ↑                           ↑
         Camera initiates          Minimal resource usage
         (works behind NAT)        (< 50 MB RAM)

Zabbix Integration
Alarm Server sends events to Zabbix with format:

{event_type}|{action}|{data}|{ip}

Create a Zabbix trapper item with key alarm.event to receive events.

🛠️ Commands
Command	Description
make install	Install alarm server
make start	Start service
make stop	Stop service
make status	Check status
make logs	View logs
make test	Run tests
make monitor	Monitor events in real-time


Configure Camera
Dahua Camera
Login to camera web interface

Go to Settings → Network → Alarm Center

Configure:

Server IP: Your gateway external IP

Port: 8081

Protocol: HTTP

Enable: ✓

Go to Settings → Events → Event Settings

Enable required events:

Motion Detection

Video Loss

HDD Failure

Hikvision Camera
Login to camera web interface

Go to Configuration → Network → Advanced Settings → Alarm

Configure:

Server IP: Your gateway external IP

Port: 8081

Protocol: HTTP

Enable: ✓

Step 4: Configure Zabbix
Create Host
Login to Zabbix web interface

Go to Data collection → Hosts → Create host

Fill:

Host name: Alarm_Receiver

Groups: Cameras

Monitored by proxy: (your proxy if any)

Create Item
On host Alarm_Receiver, go to Items → Create item

Fill:

Name: Alarm Events

Type: Zabbix trapper

Key: alarm.event

Type of information: Text

History: 90d

Create Triggers (Optional)
Trigger	Expression
Motion Detected	find(/Alarm_Receiver/alarm.event,,"like","Motion")=1
Video Loss	find(/Alarm_Receiver/alarm.event,,"like","VideoLoss")=1
HDD Error	find(/Alarm_Receiver/alarm.event,,"like","HDD")=1
         
Configuration Parameters
HTTP Server
Parameter	Description	Default
port	Listening port for HTTP alarms	8081
debug	Enable debug logging	false
Dahua Private Protocol
Parameter	Description	Default
enabled	Enable private protocol support	true
ports	List of ports to listen	[37777, 37778]
debug	Enable debug logging	false
Hisilicon
Parameter	Description	Default
enabled	Enable Hisilicon support	true
port	Listening port	15002
debug	Enable debug logging	false
Zabbix
Parameter	Description	Default
server	Zabbix server address	192.168.80.7
port	Zabbix server port	10051
sender	Path to zabbix_sender	/usr/bin/zabbix_sender
Logging
Parameter	Description	Default
level	Log level	INFO
file	Log file path	/var/log/alarm_receiver/receiver.log
Port Selection
Avoid using ports 80-90, 8080-8090, 160-170 (conflict with other services)

Recommended ports:

HTTP: 8081

Private: 37777, 37778

Hisilicon: 15002

FTP: 2121
